The paper presents distributed algorithms for problems in the congested clique model, which is a well-studied model in distributed computing. The algorithms are designed to achieve near-constant time complexity, which is a key focus of research in the field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with metric facility location and minimum spanning tree problems, which are classic problems in computer science, and hence, it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The algorithms presented in the paper are designed to work in a network setting, and hence, it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
